ZH: 我们应该携带身份证明以便进入国家公园。
EN: We should carry identification cards to enter the national park.

ZH: 学生在校内必须携带校园通行证。
EN: Students must carry their campus ID cards while on campus.

ZH: 我常常携带一个小包包，里面放着日常用品。
EN: I often carry a small bag with everyday items inside.

ZH: 骑自行车时，应该携带头盔以保护头部安全。
EN: When riding a bicycle, it is important to wear a helmet for head protection.

ZH: 旅行时最好携带一张地图以方便导航。
EN: It is advisable to carry a map when traveling for easy navigation.

ZH: 她从来不携带现金，只用信用卡支付。
EN: She never carries cash, only pays with credit cards.

ZH: 需要携带一件外套以便应对变化的天气。
EN: It is necessary to bring a jacket to cope with changing weather.

ZH: 在登机前，务必携带护照和登机牌。
EN: It is essential to carry your passport and boarding pass before boarding.

ZH: 包里通常携带着我的钱包、手机和钥匙。
EN: My bag usually holds my wallet, cellphone, and keys.

ZH: 他总是携带一支笔和便签纸，以便随时记录重要的事情。
EN: He always carries a pen and a notepad to jot down important things anytime.

ZH: 工作时，我总是携带一个笔记本电脑以便处理文件。
EN: I always bring a laptop with me to work for handling documents.

ZH: 现场考试时，学生只能携带必备的文具。
EN: During on-site exams, students can only bring necessary stationery.

ZH: 在这个城市，人们晚上外出一定要携带防身工具。
EN: In this city, people must carry self-defense tools when going out at night.

ZH: 游客必须携带有效的签证才能进入该国境内。
EN: Tourists must have a valid visa to enter the country.

ZH: 在火车上，乘客需要携带车票以示身份。
EN: Passengers need to carry their tickets as identification on the train.

ZH: 我每天都携带一瓶水，以保持身体水份充足。
EN: I carry a bottle of water with me every day to keep myself hydrated.

ZH: 去野外旅行要携带一些食物，以备不时之需。
EN: It's important to bring some food when going on outdoor trips in case of emergencies.

ZH: 他经常携带一本书来打发时间。
EN: He often carries a book to pass the time.

ZH: 健身时，我会携带一条毛巾以便擦汗。
EN: I bring a towel to wipe off sweat when working out.

ZH: 在户外活动中，应该携带一些急救药品以备不时之需。
EN: It is advisable to carry some first aid supplies for emergencies during outdoor activities.
